verses.roman:
eta kahi' dui jane vidāya la-ila
gopīnātha, vāṇīnātha-duṅhe saṅge nila

synonyms: eta kahi'-saying this; dui jane—both of them; vidāya la-ila—took leave; gopīnātha—Gopīnātha Ācārya; vāṇīnātha—Vāṇīnātha Rāya; duṅhe saṅge nila—took both of them with them.
translation: Saying this, Kāśī Miśra and the temple inspector took their leave, and Gopīnātha and Vāṇīnātha went with them.
